============================================================
Implementation summary (28 REQ-DX-* satisfied)
============================================================

1. `blockrun commands [--json]` (REQ-DX-001..008):
   - src/core/introspect-schema.ts — introspectSchema(schema): FlagMeta[], pure zod
     4.4.3 runtime introspection (no hand-maintained flag catalog).
   - src/core/cost-model.ts — COMMAND_COST_MODEL derived by grepping each real
     src/commands/<name>.ts source for `gatePaidCall(` at module-load time (no
     hand-typed free/paid list).
   - src/core/commands-catalog.ts — buildCommandsCatalog(program) reads the LIVE
     Commander `program.commands` array for name/description (the exact --help text,
     not a copy), joins introspectSchema() + COMMAND_COST_MODEL per command.
   - src/core/commands-render.ts — pure --json / human-table rendering (deliberately
     placed under src/core/, NOT src/commands/, since it is not one of the 18 REAL
     gatePaidCall-eligible commands PROP-DX-007/014 enumerate).
   - src/index.ts — registers `commands` last, WITHOUT withCommon() (REQ-DX-008: no
     --budget-limit/--agent-id — meaningless for a free, local-only command).

2. Error `code` + exit-code taxonomy (REQ-DX-010..017):
   - src/core/errors.ts — extractErrorMessage() now detects err.cause.code
     (ECONNREFUSED/ENOTFOUND/ETIMEDOUT/EAI_AGAIN) or reuses shell/http.ts's
     isTimeoutError(), appending a "(network:...)" marker (REQ-DX-015). formatError()'s
     3 inline classification consts extracted into exported classifyKnownError(),
     same real branch order (REQ-DX-016).
   - src/core/error-classification.ts — classifyErrorCode(message) pattern-matches
     network_error / quote_exceeded / budget_exceeded / (via classifyKnownError)
     upstream_error / insufficient_funds, else the no-code fallback (exit 1).
   - src/core/render.ts — fail()/renderError() is the ONE shared classification
     chokepoint (REQ-DX-014): computes code+exitCode via classifyErrorCode()
     automatically, OR uses an explicit `opts.code` override for the ONE
     structurally-detected case classifyErrorCode cannot derive from message text
     alone (usage_error — validation messages are too heterogeneous across 18
     src/args/*.ts files to share a pattern).
   - All 18 src/commands/<name>.ts: `if (!built.ok) return fail(built.error,
     opts.json, { code: "usage_error" });` (mechanical, identical 1-line edit per
     file, mirroring the buildRequest-rejection line REQ-DX-011 item 1 cites).
   - src/commands/dex.ts (REQ-DX-017): catch block now calls extractErrorMessage(err)
     instead of the old inline `err.message`/String(err) shortcut — the ONE command
     that needed this fix.

3. `balanceUnavailableReason` (REQ-DX-020..024):
   - src/shell/wallet.ts — getChainBalance()/getBaseUsdcBalance()/
     getSolanaUsdcBalance() now return { balance: number | null; reason?:
     "all_rpcs_failed" | "solana_client_error" } instead of a bare number | null.
   - src/commands/wallet.ts — `status` action's base/solana sub-objects and `chain`
     action's activeBalance both gain balanceUnavailableReason, present ONLY when
     that balance is null (spread-conditionally, so a real 0 balance carries no
     reason key at all). Human (non --json) status text appends "(reason)" for a
     null balance.

4. Docs (REQ-DX-030..034):
   - README.md — 19th Commands-table row for `commands`; new "Machine-readable
     errors: code and exit codes" subsection (all 6 code values + 0/1/2/3/4 mapping,
     no invented 7th value); Environment Variables / budget-delegation sections
     untouched.
   - PARITY.md — new "Known non-parity points" bullet: `blockrun commands` has no
     MCP-tool equivalent. The 18 existing `### <command>` sections unchanged.
   - scripts/docs-check.mjs (blockrun-cli-docs feature's own regression script, owned
     by that feature, not by agent-dx) — updated for the new REAL 19-command set:
     the top-level gate and PROP-002 (README Commands table) now expect 19; PROP-012
     (PARITY.md per-command MCP-parity sections) explicitly EXCLUDES `commands` from
     its 18-section check (REQ-DX-033: `commands` has no MCP tool to mirror, so it
     gets a non-parity bullet, not a `### commands` section — this exclusion is
     REQUIRED, not a workaround).

5. Regression / money-path (REQ-DX-040, REQ-DX-NG-001..005):
   - No change to payment signing, budget arithmetic (checkBudget/reserveBudget/
     recordActualSpend), or which upstream endpoint any command calls.
   - No existing ok()-path JSON field renamed/removed; only balanceUnavailableReason
     was ADDED (REQ-DX-NG-002).
   - Existing error JSON's `message` field content/meaning unchanged for every case
     except network_error, whose message gains an appended marker (REQ-DX-NG-003 —
     enrichment of a previously-uninformative "fetch failed", not a change to
     existing meaningful content).
   - `commands` makes no wallet/network call (REQ-DX-NG-005) — verified live below.

============================================================
Existing-test mock fixes required (Green-phase side effects of extending shared
modules 3 EXISTING tests already partially mock)
============================================================

- test/integration/{dex,realface,speech}.test.ts: each partially mocks
  src/shell/http.js with ONLY `fetchJson`; since src/core/errors.ts now imports
  isTimeoutError from that same module, these mocks needed `isTimeoutError:
  realIsTimeoutError` added (captured via a static import of the REAL function
  before mock.module() runs) — otherwise the mocked module lacks an export
  errors.ts genuinely needs.
- test/integration/wallet.test.ts: mocked `getChainBalance: async () => 1.23`
  (bare number, the OLD contract) — updated to `async () => ({ balance: 1.23 })`
  to match getChainBalance's new { balance, reason? } return shape.
- test/unit/balance-unavailable-reason.test.ts's 2 solana cases were split into
  their own sibling files (balance-unavailable-reason-solana-{error,success}.
  test.ts): shell/wallet.js's SolanaLLMClient import binding is fixed at that
  module's FIRST evaluation in a process — since the file's earlier base-chain
  tests already import shell/wallet.js unmocked, no LATER mock.module("@blockrun
  /llm") call in the SAME file/process could retroactively change that binding.
  Each solana case now runs in its own `node --test` file/process, mocking
  @blockrun/llm before that process's first import of shell/wallet.js (same
  top-of-file pattern test/integration/defi.test.ts already uses). Also fixed:
  spreading the real @blockrun/llm module's `default` export into namedExports
  produced invalid `export let default = ...` synthesized code (SyntaxError) —
  destructured `default` out before spreading.
- test/integration/network-error-catch-path.test.ts (Phase 2a's own PROP-DX-006
  test): switched from the global `mock.module()` to per-test `t.mock.module()`
  (2 of its 3 tests mock the same "../../src/shell/wallet.js" specifier with
  different rejection shapes — the global form throws ERR_INVALID_STATE on the
  second call); also added the same isTimeoutError re-export fix to its dex-case
  http.js mock.

