CAVEAT (read before treating this as a regression): PROP-016/016b are
blockrun-cli-docs's OWN "git diff since THAT feature's init commit is limited to an
allow-listed set of doc/meta files, src/ untouched beyond one version-literal line"
regression guard — `FEATURE_NAME` inside docs-check.mjs is hardcoded to
"blockrun-cli-docs" and the diff base is that (now long-completed, v1.0.0-tagged)
feature's own init commit. blockrun-cli-agent-dx is a DELIBERATE, separate, real
src/ implementation feature (unlike blockrun-cli-docs) — the moment ANY such
feature lands real src/ changes on top of blockrun-cli-docs's init commit, PROP-016/
016b's check is mathematically guaranteed to report the new src/ files as
"disallowed," by the design of that check, not by any omission here. This was
expected going in (Feature 2's own spec explicitly says it is an src/
implementation feature) and is not something a narrower allow-list edit can fix
without defeating that check's actual regression-testing purpose for future
re-verification of blockrun-cli-docs alone. The other 16/18 checks — which test
REAL, still-applicable invariants (Commands table completeness, PARITY.md section
completeness, forbidden terms, etc.) — all genuinely pass.
